# Rust Backend Architecture

Policy: `.ai/policies/backend-rust.md`

## Crates

```
domain ← application ← adapters-http | adapters-persistence ← infrastructure
```

- `domain`: business rules, money types, invariants — no HTTP/ORM/framework deps
- `application`: use cases, ports, orchestration
- `contracts`: API DTOs / OpenAPI types
- `adapters-http`: thin Axum handlers
- `adapters-persistence`: ORM, repos, migrations
- `infrastructure`: config, telemetry, clients

## Money (Product Critical)

- Integer minor units
- DB transactions for transfers
- Idempotency keys on transfer API
- Append-only ledger for audit
- Tests: 100 concurrent transfers + duplicate idempotency key

## Handlers

Validate → map to command → execute use case → map response. No business logic in handlers.

## Quality Gates

```bash
cargo fmt --check
cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings
cargo test
```

Optional when configured: `cargo nextest run`, `cargo deny check`, `cargo audit`.

## Prohibited

ORM entities in domain; skipped migrations; undocumented `allow(clippy::...)` bypasses.
